Package: citenets
Title: Citation, Co-Citation, and Bibliometric Network Construction
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Mohammed", "Saqr", , "saqr@saqr.me", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5881-3109"))
Description: Constructs bibliometric networks from scholarly data using
    state-of-the-art counting and normalization methods. Supports
    co-citation, bibliographic coupling, co-authorship, keyword
    co-occurrence, and direct citation networks. Implements full counting,
    fractional counting (Perianes-Rodriguez et al., 2016), and paper-level
    fractional counting (Batagelj & Cerinsek, 2013) via two-mode network
    multiplication. Normalizations include association strength (van Eck &
    Waltman, 2009), Salton's cosine, Jaccard, inclusion index, and
    equivalence index. Reads Scopus, Web of Science, OpenAlex, BibTeX,
    RIS, and Lens.org formats.
